# Package.json Metadata Standards

## Required Metadata Fields

Every `package.json` must include comprehensive metadata for discoverability and professionalism:

```json
{
  "name": "project-name",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "Clear, concise description of what the package does",
  "keywords": [
    "primary-tech",
    "use-case",
    "framework",
    "platform"
  ],
  "repository": {
    "type": "git",
    "url": "https://github.com/username/repo.git"
  },
  "homepage": "https://github.com/username/repo#readme",
  "bugs": {
    "url": "https://github.com/username/repo/issues"
  },
  "author": "Your Name or GitHub Username",
  "license": "MIT",
  "private": true
}
```

## Metadata Field Guidelines

### Description

**Format:** `[Purpose] with [key features]`

**Examples:**
- ✅ "Enterprise Telegram affiliate bot with multi-level commission tracking and real-time analytics"
- ✅ "Ultra-fast web framework for edge computing with zero dependencies"
- ❌ "My cool project" (too vague)
- ❌ "Bot" (not descriptive)

**Rules:**
- Keep under 200 characters
- Include key technologies or features
- Be specific about purpose
- Avoid marketing fluff

### Keywords

**Best practices:**
- Include 10-15 relevant keywords
- Order by importance (most important first)
- Include:
  - Primary technologies (`bun`, `typescript`, `vue3`)
  - Use case (`affiliate-marketing`, `commission-tracking`)
  - Architecture (`monorepo`, `edge-computing`)
  - Platform (`cloudflare-workers`, `telegram-bot`)

```json
"keywords": [
  "telegram-bot",        // Primary tech
  "affiliate-marketing", // Use case
  "cloudflare-workers",  // Platform
  "bun",                 // Runtime
  "typescript",          // Language
  "vue3",                // Framework
  "monorepo",            // Architecture
  "commission-tracking", // Feature
  "grammy",              // Library
  "hono",                // Library
  "multi-level-marketing",
  "referral-system",
  "edge-computing",
  "d1-database",
  "turborepo"
]
```

### Repository

Always include full repository object:

```json
"repository": {
  "type": "git",
  "url": "https://github.com/username/repo.git"
}
```

**Benefits:**
- npm shows "Repository" link
- GitHub auto-detects package
- Better discoverability
- Professional appearance

### Homepage & Bugs

Link to README and issue tracker:

```json
"homepage": "https://github.com/username/repo#readme",
"bugs": {
  "url": "https://github.com/username/repo/issues"
}
```

**Alternative:**
```json
"homepage": "https://yourproject.com",  // If you have a website
"bugs": {
  "url": "https://github.com/username/repo/issues",
  "email": "support@yourproject.com"   // Optional
}
```

### Author

Options:

```json
// Simple string
"author": "Your Name"

// With email
"author": "Your Name <your.email@example.com>"

// Full object
"author": {
  "name": "Your Name",
  "email": "your.email@example.com",
  "url": "https://yourwebsite.com"
}

// Multiple authors
"contributors": [
  "Person One <one@example.com>",
  "Person Two <two@example.com>"
]
```

### License

**Common licenses:**
- `"MIT"` - Most permissive, recommended for open source
- `"ISC"` - Similar to MIT, simpler text
- `"Apache-2.0"` - Patent protection
- `"UNLICENSED"` - Private/proprietary
- `"SEE LICENSE IN LICENSE.txt"` - Custom license

**Always include LICENSE file in repository root!**

## Scripts Organization

### Naming Conventions

Use clear, consistent prefixes:

```json
"scripts": {
  // Development
  "dev": "...",
  "dev:bot": "...",
  "dev:api": "...",
  "dev:ui": "...",
  
  // Building
  "build": "...",
  "build:api": "...",
  "build:ui": "...",
  
  // Testing
  "test": "...",
  "test:unit": "...",
  "test:e2e": "...",
  "test:coverage": "...",
  
  // Deployment
  "deploy": "...",
  "deploy:staging": "...",
  "deploy:prod": "...",
  
  // Quality checks
  "lint": "...",
  "format": "...",
  "type-check": "...",
  
  // Cleanup
  "clean": "...",
  "clean:cache": "...",
  "clean:build": "...",
  
  // Database
  "db:create": "...",
  "db:migrate": "...",
  "db:seed": "..."
}
```

### Script Prefixes

| Prefix | Purpose | Examples |
|--------|---------|----------|
| `dev:` | Development servers | `dev:bot`, `dev:api` |
| `build:` | Build processes | `build:api`, `build:ui` |
| `test:` | Testing | `test:unit`, `test:e2e` |
| `deploy:` | Deployment | `deploy:staging`, `deploy:prod` |
| `clean:` | Cleanup tasks | `clean:cache`, `clean:build` |
| `db:` | Database operations | `db:migrate`, `db:seed` |
| `docker:` | Docker operations | `docker:up`, `docker:logs` |
| `lint:` | Linting | `lint:js`, `lint:css` |

### Script Best Practices

✅ **DO:**
```json
"scripts": {
  "dev": "bun run dev:bot",
  "dev:bot": "cd src && bun --watch index.ts",
  "test": "bun test",
  "test:watch": "bun test --watch",
  "build": "bun run build:api && bun run build:ui",
  "deploy:prod": "bun run test && bun run build && bun run deploy"
}
```

❌ **DON'T:**
```json
"scripts": {
  "start-bot": "...",        // Use dev:bot instead
  "runTests": "...",          // Use test instead (camelCase not common)
  "build_production": "...",  // Use deploy:prod instead
  "cleanup": "rm -rf *"       // Dangerous! Be specific
}
```

## Workspace Configuration (Monorepo)

For monorepos using Bun workspaces:

```json
{
  "name": "my-monorepo",
  "private": true,
  "workspaces": [
    "apps/*",
    "packages/*"
  ],
  "scripts": {
    "dev": "bun run --filter='*' dev",
    "build": "bun run --filter='*' build",
    "test": "bun run --filter='*' test"
  }
}
```

**Workspace patterns:**
- `"apps/*"` - All subdirectories in apps/
- `"packages/*"` - All subdirectories in packages/
- `"libs/**"` - Nested directories

## Dependencies Organization

### Dependency Categories

```json
{
  "dependencies": {
    // Production runtime dependencies
    "grammy": "^1.20.0",
    "hono": "^3.11.0"
  },
  "devDependencies": {
    // Development-only tools
    "@types/bun": "latest",
    "typescript": "^5.3.0",
    "vitest": "^1.0.0",
    "playwright": "^1.40.0"
  },
  "peerDependencies": {
    // Required by consumers (for libraries)
    "typescript": ">=5.0.0"
  },
  "optionalDependencies": {
    // Nice to have, won't break if missing
    "sharp": "^0.33.0"
  }
}
```

### Version Constraints

```json
{
  "dependencies": {
    "exact-version": "1.2.3",      // ❌ Avoid (too strict)
    "caret": "^1.2.3",             // ✅ Recommended (allows 1.x.x)
    "tilde": "~1.2.3",             // ⚠️ Only patch updates (1.2.x)
    "latest": "latest",            // ⚠️ Use sparingly (unstable)
    "range": ">=1.2.0 <2.0.0",    // ⚠️ Verbose
    "workspace": "workspace:*"     // ✅ For monorepo packages
  }
}
```

**Recommendations:**
- Use `^` for most dependencies (semantic versioning)
- Use `workspace:*` for internal packages in monorepos
- Pin to exact versions only when necessary (security, stability)
- Use `latest` only for types (`@types/bun`)

## Engines Field

Specify required runtime versions:

```json
{
  "engines": {
    "node": ">=18.0.0",
    "bun": ">=1.0.0"
  }
}
```

**Benefits:**
- Prevents installation with wrong runtime
- Documents minimum versions
- CI/CD validation

## Configuration Fields

### Bun-Specific

```json
{
  "bun": {
    "install": {
      "cache": true,
      "lockfile": true
    }
  }
}
```

### Type Definitions

For published packages:

```json
{
  "main": "./dist/index.js",
  "module": "./dist/index.mjs",
  "types": "./dist/index.d.ts",
  "exports": {
    ".": {
      "import": "./dist/index.mjs",
      "require": "./dist/index.js",
      "types": "./dist/index.d.ts"
    }
  }
}
```

## Publishing Configuration

For packages intended for npm/bun registry:

```json
{
  "name": "@scope/package-name",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "publishConfig": {
    "access": "public",
    "registry": "https://registry.npmjs.org/"
  },
  "files": [
    "dist",
    "README.md",
    "LICENSE"
  ]
}
```

## Monorepo Package.json Example

```json
{
  "name": "telegram-affiliate-monorepo",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "private": true,
  "description": "Enterprise Telegram affiliate bot with multi-level commission tracking",
  "keywords": [
    "telegram-bot",
    "affiliate-marketing",
    "cloudflare-workers",
    "bun",
    "typescript"
  ],
  "repository": {
    "type": "git",
    "url": "https://github.com/username/telegram-affiliate.git"
  },
  "homepage": "https://github.com/username/telegram-affiliate#readme",
  "bugs": {
    "url": "https://github.com/username/telegram-affiliate/issues"
  },
  "author": "Your Name",
  "license": "MIT",
  "workspaces": [
    "apps/*",
    "packages/*"
  ],
  "scripts": {
    "dev": "bun run --filter='*' dev",
    "build": "bun run --filter='*' build",
    "test": "bun test",
    "lint": "prettier --check .",
    "format": "prettier --write .",
    "type-check": "tsc --noEmit",
    "deploy:prod": "bun run test && bun run build && bun run deploy"
  },
  "devDependencies": {
    "@types/bun": "latest",
    "typescript": "^5.3.0",
    "prettier": "^3.1.0",
    "vitest": "^1.0.0"
  },
  "engines": {
    "bun": ">=1.0.0"
  }
}
```

## Child Package Example (apps/api/package.json)

```json
{
  "name": "api",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "private": true,
  "scripts": {
    "dev": "bun src/index.ts",
    "build": "bun build src/index-worker.ts --outdir dist",
    "deploy:staging": "wrangler deploy --env staging",
    "deploy:prod": "wrangler deploy --env production"
  },
  "dependencies": {
    "hono": "^3.11.0",
    "@affiliate/schemas": "workspace:*"
  },
  "devDependencies": {
    "wrangler": "^3.20.0"
  }
}
```

## Validation Checklist

Before committing package.json changes:

- [ ] Description is clear and under 200 characters
- [ ] 10-15 relevant keywords included
- [ ] Repository URL is correct
- [ ] Homepage links to README or website
- [ ] Bugs URL points to issue tracker
- [ ] Author field is filled
- [ ] License matches LICENSE file
- [ ] Scripts use consistent naming (prefix:action)
- [ ] Dependencies use `^` for versions
- [ ] Workspace packages use `workspace:*`
- [ ] Engines field specifies minimum versions
- [ ] No hardcoded secrets or tokens
- [ ] JSON is valid (no trailing commas!)

## Common Mistakes to Avoid

❌ **DON'T:**
```json
{
  "name": "my-app",           // Too generic
  "description": "",          // Missing
  "keywords": [],             // Empty
  "author": "",               // Missing
  "license": "UNLICENSED",   // For private only
  "scripts": {
    "start": "node .",        // Ambiguous
    "cleanup": "rm -rf *"     // Dangerous!
  }
}
```

✅ **DO:**
```json
{
  "name": "telegram-affiliate-bot",
  "description": "Multi-level affiliate tracking bot for Telegram",
  "keywords": ["telegram", "affiliate", "bot"],
  "author": "Your Name",
  "license": "MIT",
  "scripts": {
    "dev:bot": "bun --watch src/index.ts",
    "clean:cache": "bun pm cache clean"
  }
}
```

